-10- Preconditions: A handle referring to the coroutine whose promise object
is *this is at the top of *active_ of some generator
object x. The coroutine referred to by g.range.coroutine_
is suspended at its initial suspend point.


-11- Returns: An awaitable object of an unspecified type ()
into which g.range is moved, whose member await_ready returns false,
whose member await_suspend pushes g.range.coroutine_ into *x.active_
and resumes execution of the coroutine referred to by g.range.coroutine_,
and whose member await_resume evaluates rethrow_exception(except_)
if bool(except_) is true. If bool(except_) is false,
the await_resume member has no effects.


-12- Remarks: A yield-expression that calls
this functionone of these functions has type
void ().
